contentrichtext.text: '''Zenger''' may refer to: * [[Christoph Zenger]] (born 1940, Lindau), a German mathematician * [[Erich Zenger]] (1939, Dollnstein - 2010, Münster), a German Roman Catholic priest and theologian * [[John Peter Zenger]] (1697–1746), a German-American printer, publisher, editor, and journalist * [[Josef Zenger]] (born 1935, Herzogenaurach), German football player<ref>[[:de:Josef Zenger]]</ref> * [[Joseph Zenger]] (1757, Straubing - 1827, Passau), German Catholic priest<ref>[[:de:Joseph Zenger]]</ref> * [[Karl Zenger]] (1873, Erding - 1912, Haar, Bavaria), a German figure skater * [[Karl Zenger (architect)|Karl (Gustav Ritter von) Zenger]] (1838, Erolzheim - 1905), German architect<ref>[[:de:Karl Zenger]]</ref> * [[Stephan van Zenger]] (1501, Graz - 1532, Vienna), son of [[Georg Wispeck von Velburg]] and [[Elisabeth van Zenger]]<ref>[[:de:Stephan van Zenger]]</ref> * [[Wilhelm Zenger]] (? - 1911), a German figure skater * [[The Lonesome Death of Hattie Carroll|Williamson Zenger]] * [[Andrew Hamilton (lawyer)#Zenger case|Andrew Hamilton]] and [[William Cosby#The Zenger case|William Cosby]] on ''Zenger case'' == References == {{Reflist}} {{surname|Zenger, van Zenger}} [[Category:German-language surnames]]
